19/06/2003
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Serbian Justice Minister Vladam Batic, who also heads the constitutional commission, said Wednesday (18 June) that a referendum on the Serbian Constitution should be held on 15 February. Despite setbacks, Batic said that the constitution should be adopted by year's end.
In other news, the UN war crimes tribunal reiterated on Wednesday that former Bosnian Serb commander Gen Ratko Mladic is either living in Serbia-Montenegro or visiting often. Prosecution spokeswoman Florence Hartmann insisted that local authorities remain obligated to detain and extradite Mladic and any other indictees. (Tanjug, BBC, B92, FoNet - 18/06/03)
